// Sidebar composition demo
---

<div class="flow flow-space-md">
    <h2>Sidebar Composition</h2>
    <p>
        The sidebar composition creates a layout with a fixed-width sidebar and
        flexible main content. When space is limited, the sidebar and main
        content stack vertically.
    </p>

    <div>
        <aside class="sidebar sidebar-size-xs">
            <h3>Sidebar</h3>
            <nav>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <a href="#" class="link"> Dashboard </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="#" class="link"> Profile </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <a href="#" class="link"> Settings </a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </nav>
        </aside>
        <main>
            <h3>Main Content</h3>
            <p>
                This is the main content area. It takes up the remaining space
                and wraps to full width when the container is too narrow to fit
                both sidebar and content.
            </p>
            <p>
                The sidebar composition is perfect for dashboards, documentation
                sites, and any layout needing a persistent navigation area.
            </p>
        </main>
    </div>

    <div>
        <aside class="sidebar sidebar-size-lg">
            <h3>Filters</h3>
            <div class="flow flow-space-sm">
                <label>
                    <input type="checkbox" /> Option 1
                </label>
                <label>
                    <input type="checkbox" /> Option 2
                </label>
                <label>
                    <input type="checkbox" /> Option 3
                </label>
            </div>
        </aside>
        <main>
            <h3>Results</h3>
            <p>Filtered content would appear here.</p>
        </main>
    </div>
</div>
